    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-07T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-07T01:35:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Amiranian/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-07T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 7, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 7—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. My 56, May 29, 11 a.m. Clapp informs me he may accept tentative offer of
                    Iranian authorities subject to Shah’s approval to appoint him Chief of
                    Geological Survey with special reference to petroleum. I see no objection as the
                    continuation of such contacts may prove helpful to American interests in
                    general.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
